AI Overview
Splitwise is the top choice for recording and sharing expenses, specializing in tracking shared bills, rent, and trip costs to show who owes what. It offers a user-friendly interface to scan receipts and manage ongoing balances, available for free on iOS, Android, and web. 
Here are the best cost-sharing and expense recording apps available in 2026:
Best Overall Expense Tracking Apps

    Splitwise: Best for roommates and ongoing expenses. It has a "running balance" model that tracks who paid what over months or years.
    Splid: Best for group trips and vacations. It works offline and does not require account registration.
    Tricount: A 100% free app, ideal for group trips and casual, quick expense tracking.
    Settle Up: Excellent for mixed-platform groups (Android, iOS, Windows, Web) and handles weighted, uneven splits efficiently. 

Specialized & Niche Apps

    Cino: An innovative app that uses a shared virtual card to split payments at the moment of purchase, eliminating the need to pay upfront.
    Tab: Best for scanning restaurant receipts, allowing users to tap items they ordered to split the bill, including tax and tip.
    SharedExpenseTracker: A Windows-based system, useful for tracking shared household expenses.
    GEM - Split Expenses: A clean, offline-friendly alternative to Splitwise. 

Key Features to Look For

    Receipt Scanning: Allows taking photos of receipts to capture data automatically (often in Pro versions).
    Offline Access: Essential for international travel (e.g., Splid).
    Multiple Currencies: Converts expenses for international trips automatically.
    Settle-Up Calculation: Minimizes the number of transactions required to pay everyone back. 

